
1. Malawi is a landlocked country about the size of Pennsylvania.
2. Lake Malawi, formerly Lake Nyasa, occupies most of the country's eastern border.
3. The north-south Rift Valley is flanked by mountain ranges and high plateau areas.
4. In 1884, Cecil Rhodes's British South African Company received a charter to develop the country.
5. On July 6, 1964, Nyasaland became the independent nation of Malawi.
6.